# Parallel agents (auto-routing — mandatory)

When a request has **two or more independent deliverables**, the parent agent **must** launch **Task** subagents **in parallel in a single message** before or alongside parent work. **Do not** default to serial single-agent execution.

## Auto-parallel triggers (any match → parallelize)

| Trigger | Example |
|---------|---------|
| Vault + repo in one ask | Obsidian doc + `scripts/` change |
| Doc + draft + code | Runbook + blog draft + pipeline fix |
| Explore + implement | Read-only audit while editing elsewhere |
| 3+ numbered deliverables | "1. GSC 2. P0–P4 3. vault doc 4. draft" |
| User says parallel / batch / "and also" | Explicit or implicit multi-output |
| Independent trees | SEO audit + vault session note |

## Subagent routing table

| Work | `subagent_type` | Notes |
|------|-----------------|-------|
| Vault markdown, ops notes, blog drafts | `vault-writer` | Never write drafts to `content/posts/` |
| Broad codebase search | `explore` | `medium` or `very thorough` |
| Git, npm, deploy shell | `shell` | |
| Post-ship diff review | `code-reviewer` | After substantive edits |
| Footer shape check | `footer-auditor` | Readonly |
| General multi-step when no specialist fits | `generalPurpose` | |

**Launch rule:** Multiple Task calls in **one** parent message. Pass full context — subagents do not see parent chat history.

## Do NOT parallelize

- Single-file or single-question fix
- Step B depends on step A output (e.g. fix then verify same file)
- User asked for one focused answer (Mode A/B)
- Security-sensitive sequential review required

## Footer contract

Modes **C–G:** field **Agents** must list subagent names + one-line why, or `none — single-agent` only when triggers above did not apply.

